Functional KPSS Test

kpss_test.Rd

Compute the KPSS statistic for functional data.

Usage

kpss_test(
  X,
  method = c("MC", "block", "sliding"),
  M = 1000,
  h = 3,
  TVE = 1,
  replace = TRUE
)

Arguments

X

A dfts object or data which can be automatically converted to that format. See dfts().

method

String (default MC) for the method: monte carlo simulation (MC), block permutation (block), and sliding window permutation (sliding)

M

Number of simulations (default 1000) to estimate theoretical distribution

h

Numeric (default 3) for the block size when using a permutation test

TVE

Numeric (default 1) for selecting the number of principle components / eigenvalues

replace

Boolean (default TRUE) to indicate if blocks should be selected with replacement when using a permutation test

Value

List with statistic, p-value and theoretical simulations, respectively

References

Chen, Y., & Pun, C. S. (2019). A bootstrap-based KPSS test for functional time series. Journal of Multivariate Analysis, 174, 104535.

Kokoszka, P., & Young, G. (2016). KPSS test for functional time series. Statistics, 50(5), 957-973.
